OUR MISSION

Warrior Wellness Program (WWP) provides an opportunity for healing for those affected by the traumas of war. Through effective alternative therapies and community engagement our goal is to promote a healthy, connected and resilient veteran and military population.

ALABAMA LOCATION
Play Video

Who We Are

Warrior Wellness Program is a 501(c)(3) providing alternative therapy services and community engagement to
our past and present military population. Warrior Wellness Program understands the transition from military to
civilian life can be difficult. We exist to provide timely and effective treatment, engagement, and support for
those who are ready to tackle their challenges and live a full and productive life beyond military service.

 

TESTIMONIALS

What People Are Saying

"I experienced benefits after my first ART session, it has been the most effective therapy in treating and resolving the many combat related traumas haunting my daily life."
US NAVY COMBAT VETERAN
This is not a testimony to state that I am cured of all my ailments but a testimony that I can live with them today and find peace. I am more than glad to say as of today my life has made a 180*. I went through the program as a broken, silent, and homeless veteran. I, with help of this program, have been able to target my problems and found a way to heal. Never did I dream it possible to not have to carry the burdens and pain of my past but today, I do not. Thank you Warrior Wellness for your service to all those who have served!
US AIRFORCE COMBAT VETERAN
I've attended many different therapies, and this was hands down the best I've ever received. Your dedication to helping people is top notch!! Until we meet again, take care and please continue your amazing work. Thank you from the bottom of my heart for the life changing experience.
US ARMY COMBAT VETERAN
I came into this hopefully open and left feeling wonderfully surprised at truly what a difference I felt only after a week. I pushed myself to get all I could from this program and I'm so happy I did. ART was shockingly effective and I've been using the IRest daily too. The authenticity and dedication of everyone involved (staff and volunteers) is truly touching. It allowed me to be open, vulnerable and all while feeling strong. I hope Warrior Wellness can continue to positively impact the lives of veterans and their families for many years ahead.
US ARMY COMBAT VETERAN
It truly was a transformative experience for me, things I have been struggling with for years that no amount of medication, therapy, hospital stays has been able to touch are no longer an issue for me. For the first time in years my mental health is no longer a daily struggle. I can’t thank you all enough for the work you do.
